The paper deals with online learning and ranking of items, which is a common problem in machine learning and information retrieval. The focus is on the performance of the system under a novel top-1 feedback model, which is relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of popular ranking measures such as PairwiseLoss and DCG, which are relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents results on the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which is relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
